	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As far as I know there are no clones that are an exact replica.  Instead of using multiple chips they use a single chip (NOAC NesOnAChip).  It is much cheaper than having multiple chips, but they rely on their own programming and therefore differ from original hardware programming.  The USB CopyNES requires you to desolder the original CPU and attach it to the CopyNES board, so that eliminates all famiclones/NOAC consoles.
<br />
<br />Besides, nothing beats the accuracy and authentic feel of the original IMO.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


