		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">[My EPROM emulator] cost me a small fortune at the time, I think almost $200, but was well worth it.<br /><br />It's great because with this you can totally ditch NES emulators.</div><br />How well does your EPROM emulator support single-stepping or breakpoints or watchpoints?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I also much rather prefer not having to alt+tab around between crap when I could just be writing the code and only have to hit 1 key</div>
<br />I configured Gedit on my Ubuntu laptop so that when I press F5 in a project's source code folder, it looks for a  makefile in the parent folder and runs it. The default action of this makefile is to build the iNES ROM and run it in an FCE Ultra window. To go back to the editor code, I need only press Esc.
<br />
<br />Each method has its advantages: yours works for custom mapper development, and mine works on the bus.

		

